data.criteria: After duplicate removal, all titles and abstracts were screened for potential eligibility after which full text articles were assessed for eligibility. Study selection was performed by two independent researchers (K.K.W. and L.M.F.). Interrater reliability is reported for the initial agreement on full text eligibility where values of kappa are rated as fair (κ = 0.4–0.59), good (κ = 0.6–0.74), or excellent (κ > 0.75).47 Disagreement was resolved through discussion. If no consensus could be achieved, a third researcher was consulted (D.D.E.).
